quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  61,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth halloweth Allah. And He is the Mighty, the Wise"
  61,2,O ye who believe! wherefore say ye that which ye do not
  61,3,Most odious it is Unto Allah that ye should Say that which ye do not
  61,4,"Verily Allah loveth those who fight in His way drown up in ranks, as though they were a structure well compacted"
  61,5,"And recall what time Musa said Unto his people: O my people! wherefore hurt ye me, When surely ye know that verily I am Allah's apostle Unto you! Then when they sweryed, Allah made their hearts swerve; and Allah guideth not a transgressing people"
  61,6,"And recall what time Isa, son of Maryam, said: children of Israi'l! verily I am Allah's apostle Unto you, confirming the Taurat which was before me, and giving the glad tidings of an apostle who cometh after me: his name will be Ahmad. Then when he brought Unto them evidences, they said: this is magic manifest"
  61,7,And who is a greater wrong-doer than he who fabricateth against Allah a lie even as he is summoned Unto Islam? And Allah guideth not a wrongdoing people
  61,8,"Fain would they extinguish the light of Allah is with their mouths and Allah is going to perfect His light, even though averse may be the infidels"
  61,9,"He it is Who hath sent His apostle with the guidance and the true religion, that He may make it triumph over all religion, even though averse may be associaters"